cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the dynamics of knowledge building in a crowdsourced environment, specifically through the use of a customized Crowdsourced Annotation System (CAS) and analysis of datasets from Wikipedia and Stack Overflow. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including Cybernetics (cs.CY) for the study of complex systems, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the analysis of social interactions in crowdsourcing, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) for the design of crowdsourced systems, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) for the extraction of knowledge from crowdsourced data, and Sound (cs.SD) for the use of annotations in audio data. However, given the focus on social interactions and knowledge building, cs.CY and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
